commit.message:
Set vsn to 1.2.0 to make rebar3 hex publish happy

Don't ask me why!
Fix necessary options for hex in luerl.app and set new version 1.2
Improve formatting of error messages for output

Add OTP 21,22,23 to be checked when commiting

This should work now!

Make calls to atom_to_binary of 2 argument specific utf8

Older versions of Erlang did not have the atom_to_binary/1 so this
will be safer with older OTP versions.

Final test

If this doesn't work we give it up.
Use the CATCH macro in try/catch

Add OTP 20,21,22,23 to be checked when commiting

Hopefully it will work this time. Last attempt.

Remove OTP 21,22,13 as they did not work

I will add them again when I find out why they did not work.
Rename #if_stmt.else to else_block to support Erlang/OTP 27.0-rc1
Add OTP 21,22,23 to be checked when commiting
Add support for OTP under 25
Add CT suite for os.date in different Time Zones
Fix function to use ~ts to get the messages right

Fix the error call, its error message and its handling in pcall

Its function is now called error_call as is the error it generates.
Removed test which seemed locale dependant

Make date handling in os library calls more compatible with Lua

Also added a few extra options and restructured the file a bit. There
are even more alternatives but it gets messy with the locale you are
in.

Add testing to Makefile, remove cover from rebar.config.script

For some mysterious reason the coverage analysis completely crashes
when run from make. Will returned when we know why.
Update luerl.app.src
Added logo and badges to README.
Updates for CI/CD.
Simple formating tweaks.

Fix format_error to correctly generate utf-8 encoded binaries

Not that the caller must be aware when outputing them, e.g. output
using '~ts' option in io:format.

Fix Lua strings to correctly handle utf-8 encoding

The utf-8 encoding can bot occur in binaries and in iolists. The user
must be aware of this, e.g output using '~ts' option in io:format.

Added logos to repo.

Also: ensured they don't get packaged when uploaded to hex.pm.

Fix multi line strings so they handle utf8 encoding properly

Of course the multi line string must handle ut8 encoding as well.

Fix so that numeric operations return Luerl errors

Before errors in numeric operations would just cause the emulator to
crash with an erlang error now it returns a relevant Luerl error.

Fix the file loading functions so they handle errors correctly

They now return the error value with a message string.

Add [=[ ]=], [==[ ]==] and [===[ ]===] multi line strings

Unfortunately the scanner only allows us to give versions of the mulit
line scanners as it work on regular expressions.

Make a little more complinat for use with rebar3

So far very simple but hopefully this will help a bit.
